article.headline: McCoughtry leads Louisville past DePaul
article.linkText: McCoughtry pours in 29 to lead Louisville past DePaul
article.story:
LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- Angel McCoughtry scored 29 points to lead four players in double figures as Louisville (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) cruised to an 86-68 win over DePaul on Saturday.

McCoughtry shot 11-of-20 from the field, made all seven of her free throws and added 12 rebounds for the Cardinals (21-2, 7-2 Big East). Jazz Covington scored 14 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Yuliya Tokova added 13 points. Reserve Chauntise Wright went 7-for-7 from the field to finish with 15 points for Louisville.

Louisville lead 38-37 at halftime, then went on a 15-3 run midway through the second half to break the game open.

DePaul (14-9, 4-6) lost its second straight. Allie Quigley led the Blue Demons with 24 points and Jenna Rubino added 16.
